{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Manages PID files for tracking running virtual machines.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"PIDFile","kind":"identifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each running VM writes a PID file at"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"~\/.spooktacular\/vms\/<name>.vm\/pid"},{"type":"text","text":". The file contains the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"process ID of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start"},{"type":"text","text":" process that owns the VM."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Other commands ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"stop"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"list"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ip"},{"type":"text","text":") read the PID file to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"determine whether a VM is running and to signal the process."}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"PID-File-Lifecycle","text":"PID File Lifecycle"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start"},{"type":"text","text":" writes the PID file before booting the VM."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook stop"},{"type":"text","text":" reads the PID file and sends SIGTERM."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start"},{"type":"text","text":" installs a SIGTERM handler that gracefully"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"stops the VM, removes the PID file, and exits."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the process crashes, the PID file becomes stale."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isProcessAlive(_:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" detects stale PID files by checking","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"whether the recorded process is still running."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Thread-Safety","type":"heading","text":"Thread Safety"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All methods are static and operate on the file system. They"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are safe to call from any thread. The PID file is a plain"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"text file containing a single integer, so reads and writes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are effectively atomic at the file-system level."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/pidfile"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"sections":[],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"roleHeading":"Enumeration","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PIDFile"}],"externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit7PIDFileO","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"PIDFile","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"PIDFile","symbolKind":"enum"},"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Type-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/fileName"],"title":"Type Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isProcessAlive(_:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isRunning(bundleURL:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/read(from:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/remove(from:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/